column19:
Participant Consent Form  

	I consent to participate in this project, the details of which have been explained to me in plain language. 
	I understand that the purpose of this research is to investigate landholder preferences for conservation covenant programs. 
	I understand that my participation in this project is for research purposes only.    
	I will be required to respond to a questionnaire that asks about my land management and identifies my preferences for conservation programs.   
	I understand that my participation is voluntary and that I am free to withdraw from this project anytime without explanation or prejudice. 
	I understand that the data from this research will be stored at the University of Queensland. 
	I have been informed that the confidentiality of the information I provide will be safeguarded subject to any legal requirements; my data will be password protected and accessible only by the named researchers on the Human Ethics Application.
	I understand that after I sign this consent form, it will be retained by the researcher.

column141: I dont trust government organizations to do the right thing by me. Our council, Tweed Shire Council, is run by green mayor and 3 others who act unconscionably often. They have determined, without any consultation, that there is a koala connection through my major horticulture paddock that is clear if vegetation and had been clear for over 80 years. They can allocate wild life corridors, protected areas etc etc without any consultation with the land owner and in fact without ever telling the land owner who might find out if they submit a DA fir farm buildings, I was in a meeting where our mayor said when asked what would happen if people tried to sell the property that we will inform the new owners. I used to be interested in conservation and was about to plant 1 ha if koala trees but this council is sooooo unreliable, so divisive and so unconscionable in their conduct I refuse in any way shape or form to assist in their idiocy. They appear disinterested in any agenda but their own narrow minded idea about what should happen. They conduct community consultation because they have to but every single thing that doesnt fit with their narrow minded agenda is placed in the no further action basket. The have no understanding of generating  jobs and futures except for assisting their supporters many of whom have never actually worked for a living.

column140: Yes, including ahead of the Nov 19 bushfires which burnt around 400ha of my land.  There were also quolls and prior to the drouhgt a platypus amongst other notable creatures.  I expect the avifauna will prove to be of great interest as well as some rare flora species.
column141: The address I have provided is for one of the four parcels I own, but I have provided answers based on a balance of the verying considerations.  On one parcel I would probably accept $25/ha because it is not very accessible and of limited agricultural value.  On another with better pasture and access around $75 would be required.  The other two parcels are probably a bit of both and around $50 is reasonable to replace current earning potential.  I applied $50 as an average across all for parcels (held in two separate holdings, one on Reedy Creek Road Mole River, the other on the Bruxner Highway, Dumaresq Valley).
